This paper is about developing a new online learning algorithm for semantic parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) that involves mapping natural language sentences to their corresponding logical forms. The paper proposes a novel approach that improves the efficiency of the learning algorithm by using macro grammars and holistic triggering. 

Based on this description, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers topics related to NLP and computational linguistics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.DB (Databases), as these fields also have relevance to the development of efficient learning algorithms for NLP tasks.
